newsitem.title: SWITZERLAND: Swiss three-month money claims yield 1.760 pct.
newsitem.headline: Swiss three-month money claims yield 1.760 pct.

text.p: The Swiss federal government set terms on a new series 3.359 of three-month money market claims, which are to be paid for on November 7.
The issue, totaling 972.25 million Swiss francs, has an issue price of 99.557 percent, to yield 1.760 percent per annum.
The previous issue of three-month claims, paid for on October 24, raised 903.20 million francs and was priced at 99.654 percent to yield 1.374 percent annually.
